<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 94 / World Stock Markets: Mexico
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Stocks ended sharply higher, driven by demand from foreign investors and
expectations of a decline in interest rates.
The key IPC index climbed 65.51 points, or 3.05 per cent, to 2,213.09.
Turnover was a moderate 85.32m shares. Rises exceeded declines by 63 to 15.
Traders said the market was also helped by the strong gains on Wall Street,
which spilled over into Mexican shares trading there.
The stock exchange authorities said yesterday that the value of foreign
holdings in ADRs fell to Dollars 30bn at the end of April from Dollars
33.5bn at the beginning of the year.
</TEXT>
