<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 94 / World Stock Markets: Pakistan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FARHAN BOKHARI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ISLAMABAD
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Share prices yesterday fell for the third day, triggered by a renewal of
political uncertainty, writes Farhan Bokhari in Islamabad.
The KSE-100 index finished 71.49 weaker at 2,237.63. The index has fallen by
almost 7 per cent since Sunday following last week's violence in Karachi
which led to the death of at least 20 people.
Analysts noted that investors were also becoming cautious ahead of next
month's annual budget. COLOMBO, after four days of recovery, began heading
back towards its 1994 lows again. The CSE all-share index retreated 23.61,
or 2.3 per cent, to 1,023.95 as turn-over dropped from Rs124.6m to Rs82.9m.
</TEXT>
