<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 94 / World Commodities Prices: Copper prices beat retreat -
Market Report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
COPPER prices finished lower at the London Metal Exchange yesterday, with
the market beating a retreat from new 13-month highs on expected technical
selling and profit-taking.
The high-water mark for three months delivery was Dollars 2,097 a tonne, but
final business was at Dollars 2,073, down Dollars 4 from Monday's after
hours close.
Other metals were pulled back from artificially high levels by copper,
although ALUMINIUM proved resilient, and continued its technical
base-building above the Dollars 1,330-a-tonne level.
