<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 94 / International Company News: Top securities man quits
Republic post
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Peter Cohen, the former Shearson Lehman chairman who joined Republic New
York 18 months ago to run its new securities brokerage business, is
resigning from the banking group to set up his own investment management and
securities firm.
Mr Cohen's resignation comes two weeks after Republic decided its securities
operation should concentrate on servicing the bank's client base of
institutions and wealthy individuals, and not on developing a market-making
and underwriting franchise to compete with big Wall Street securities
houses.
Mr Cohen said yesterday he was leaving to pursue businesses, particularly
specialised securities financing and investment management. These would be
better developed by a firm that was independent of Republic, he said.
His new firm will include the operations of the Palladin Group, an
investment management company with Dollars 200m of clients' assets
specialising in non-merger arbitrage in domestic and foreign securities.
Mr Cohen is not completely severing his ties with Republic, which is 30 per
cent-owned by the Geneva-based financier Mr Edmond Safra. He will continue
to work as a consultant to the bank, which will become a minority investor
in Mr Cohen's new firm.
Mr Cohen joined Republic in November 1992, almost three years after he was
ousted as chairman of Shearson Lehman.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Republic New York Corp.
    Palladin Group.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
