<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Holmes &amp; Marchant 25% ahead
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Holmes &amp; Marchant Group, the marketing services company, reported pre-tax
profits ahead 25 per cent from Pounds 461,000 to Pounds 576,000 for the six
months to end-March.
The improvement was achieved on turnover down by Pounds 3.38m to Pounds
13.3m. Earnings per share emerged at 1.76p (1.45p). Comparative figures have
been restated to reflect the accounting policy adopted for empty leasehold
property costs.
Mr John Holmes, chairman and chief executive, said Pounds 1m of the decline
in turnover was accounted for by the closure of the group's consumer
advertising agency in February 1993, while a further Pounds 1.5m related to
client expenditure on new product launches.
With lower average borrowings in the period and a reduction in interest
rates, net interest payable was reduced from Pounds 450,000 to Pounds
350,000. Net borrowings at March 31 stood at Pounds 8.6m, an improvement of
Pounds 400,000 on the 1993 year end.
</TEXT>
