<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Bearing Power at Pounds 404,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Despite continuing pressure on margins, Bearing Power International, which
distributes precision bearings and power transmission components, raised
pre-tax profits from Pounds 257,000 to Pounds 404,000 in the half year to
March 31.
Acquisitions helped turnover jump 58 per cent to Pounds 17.9m. After a tax
charge of Pounds 120,000 (Pounds 26,000 credit), earnings per share emerged
lower at 0.84p (0.91p). There was again no interim dividend - last year's
single distribution was 0.75p.
