<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 94 / BSN changes name to Danone
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN RIDDING
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BSN, France's largest food group, is changing its name to Danone, its
leading yoghurt brand, and has unveiled several international deals,
including the FFr1.9bn (Pounds 223m) acquisition of San Miguel, one of
Spain's largest brewers.
Mr Antoine Riboud, chairman, said the change of name to Danone, the
company's strongest brand, would help the group expand internationally,
particularly into non-European markets.
Mr Riboud also announced a string of investments and acquisitions, including
the purchase of San Miguel, one of Spain's five largest brewers, with sales
last year of Pta38bn (Pounds 186m).
BSN already holds 24 per cent of the Spanish brewer and will increase its
stake to 100 per cent over the next four years.
BSN is to set up a joint venture in Russia, Danone-Volga, to produce
yoghurts and dairy produce. It is investing about FFr20m and will take an 80
per cent stake in the new company.
In Brazil, BSN is to pay an estimated FFr200m for 49 per cent of Campineira
de Alimentos, Brazil's second largest biscuit manufacturer, and in Morocco
it will pay about FFr100m for a 2.7 per cent stake in ONA, the private
sector food group. Mr Riboud hopes that non-European sales will amount to
half of total sales within 20 years, from about 9 per cent at present.
