FT  11 MAY 94 / Lack of demand closes driving test centres
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A fall in the number of learner drivers has closed 22 of the UK's 484
driving test centres. Until recently 2m people a year took a driving test,
but the figure is now 1.6m.
'Changes in the birth rate means there are fewer 17 to 18-year-olds around
and this is the main reason for the fall in test-taking numbers,' said the
Driving Standards Agency.
