</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
South West Water yesterday agreed to pay about Pounds 400,000 to settle
almost 150 claims from people who alleged they suffered long-term health
effects after drinking contaminated water six years ago. They will receive
amounts ranging from Pounds 680 to more than Pounds 10,000.
The settlement was announced in the High Court in Truro, Cornwall. The
claims came after 20 tonnes of aluminium sulphate were poured into the wrong
tank at the Lowermoor treatment works near Camelford, Cornwall.
