FT  11 MAY 94 / Zil re-opens
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LEYLA BOULTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Zil, Russia's ailing truck manufacturer, said yesterday it had reopened
after a 10-day stoppage and much political furore over its troubles, writes
Leyla Boulton. Executives at Zil, a Moscow-based enterprise with an
old-style management and 85,000 employees, said they proposed to reverse the
company's fortunes by focusing on recovering money from debtors in the
former Soviet Union, and expanding its vehicle range. They also said Zil
would take overdue steps to trim its work force. However, Professor Yevgeny
Yasin, the new economic adviser to President Boris Yeltsin, said that Zil
had managed to secure financial support from the Moscow mayor's office. Prof
Yasin stressed that the Russian government could not afford to help Zil
