<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAY 94 / International Company News: Transamerica in Dollars 200m
share buy-back move
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Transamerica, the San Francisco-based financial services group, is planning
to buy back 4.5m of its shares in a deal worth more than Dollars 200m.
Like other financial services stocks, Transamerica has been hit by rising
interest rates in recent weeks. Its shares ended last week at Dollars 51 1/8
, down from a high of Dollars 62 3/8 .
News of the buy-back spurred a rise in the stock in New York yesterday
morning, to Dollars 52 5/8 .
The company announced a Dutch auction for the stock, under which holders are
being invited to tender their shares at between Dollars 48 and Dollars 55.
Transamerica will then pay a single price for the stock it buys, set at the
lowest level which allows it to reach its target of 4.5m shares.
The offer remains open until June 6.
Standard &amp; Poor's, the ratings agency, said the company's capital structure
would remain strong even after paying out cash for the shares, and
reaffirmed its single-A senior debt rating for the group.
</TEXT>
